title: A Conversation on Privacy - Chomsky Greenwald Snowden 2016 03 25
description:
A Conversation on Privacy

The balance between national security and government intrusion on the rights of private citizens was the topic of a panel discussion featuring renowned linguist and MIT professor Noam Chomsky, NSA whistleblower Edward Snowden, and Intercept co-founding editor Glenn Greenwald. Nuala Oâ€™Connor, president and CEO of the Center for Democracy and Technology, acted as moderator.

The event was hosted in Tucson by the University of Arizona College of Behavioral Sciences on Friday, March 25, 2016.
